Ω‑CORE — UNIVERSAL REASONING KERNEL

Engineering Specification — Rev Ω.1

The Ω‑Core is the deterministic reasoning kernel of the Omricon architecture.
It validates, corrects, or halts all reasoning produced by upstream components.
The Core enforces universal invariants, ensures system stability, and guarantees deterministic behaviour across the entire pipeline.

The Ω‑Core does not interpret, structure, abstract, or perform domain reasoning.
Its function is strictly regulatory.

---

1. Core Identity

The Ω‑Core consists of three deterministic subsystems:

1. Invariant Engine
2. Lens (Minimal Correction Engine)
3. Evaluator (Reasoning Loop Controller)


These subsystems operate as a unified reasoning kernel.

---

2. Core Purpose

The Core enforces correctness and stability by:

• applying the 13 universal invariants
• validating every reasoning state
• performing minimal safe corrections
• halting when no valid reasoning path exists
• ensuring deterministic, traceable behaviour

The Core is the final authority on reasoning validity.

---

3. Core Boundaries

The Ω‑Core must not:

• reinterpret user intent (VORIN‑Ω)
• restructure content (SERA‑Ω)
• abstract content (AERION‑Ω)
• perform domain reasoning
• invent missing information
• bypass invariant checks
• continue after uncorrectable failure

The Core regulates reasoning; it does not generate it.

