5. Invariant Engine

The Invariant Engine enforces the 13 universal invariants.
Each invariant is a deterministic constraint function returning:

• PASS
• FAIL (with reason)
• NEEDS_CORRECTION

Invariants:

1. Contradiction
2. Paradox
3. Recursion
4. Drift
5. Noise
6. Structure
7. Clarity
8. Boundary
9. Stability
10. Context
11. Compression
12. Expansion
13. Universal Evaluation


These invariants define the global correctness constraints for all Omricon reasoning.

---

6. Lens — Minimal Correction Engine

The Lens performs minimal deterministic correction.

Responsibilities:

• detect missing information
• detect unsupported assumptions
• detect boundary violations
• propose minimal valid corrections
• return NO_VALID_PATH when correction is unsafe

The Lens must not rewrite meaning, restructure content, or infer missing data.

---

7. Evaluator — Reasoning Loop Controller

The Evaluator executes the Core’s deterministic evaluation loop:

1. Receive CORE_STATE
2. Run invariants
3. If all PASS → continue
4. If any FAIL → call Lens
5. If corrected → re‑evaluate
6. If still invalid → halt with explicit failure


This loop ensures:

• no drift
• no hallucination
• no unsupported inference
• no unstable reasoning

